    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "html": "üç∞ <strong>Napoleon HTTP</strong> is a small, modular HTTP server written in C ‚Äî inspired by the layered Napoleon cake. <br/> Each part of the server is a layer (transport, parser, routing, app) that can be swapped or extended."
      },
      {
        "type": "list",
        "items": [
          "Redirects: simple registry (<code>/</code> ‚Üí <code>/docs/</code>, <code>/docs</code> ‚Üí <code>/docs/</code>)",
          "Static mounts: <code>/docs</code> ‚Üí <code>./docs</code>, <code>/public</code> ‚Üí <code>./public</code>",
          "Modular design: clear separation of layers, portable to POSIX and embedded targets (WIP)"
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
